title: Every Other Weekend (1990)
overview: Camille, a mercurial César-winning actress, has seen better times. Estranged from her husband, she's with her children only every other weekend. It's her weekend, but her agent has booked her to MC a Rotary club dinner in Vichy. She takes them with her, and when her husband learns this, he demands to pick them up at once. She bolts in a rented car to the seaside, trying to improve her relations with the children, especially the precocious and distant Vincent. He loves astronomy. A rare meteor shower is due in a few days, so she suggests they go to a plateau in Spain hoping to see it. He agrees, but the relationship remains difficult, and her husband is on their trail.

Through the perspective of Sandrino, viewers journey through the various lives within a Roman apartment building, showcasing the struggles, dreams, and relationships of its inhabitants against the backdrop of an impending solar eclipse. The film uniquely blends humor and poignancy, reflecting on love, loss, and the bittersweet nature of growing up.

title: Crows and Sparrows (1949)
overview: At a Shanghai apartment, Mr Hou, a Nationalist official, gets ready to move to Taiwan upon the imminent defeat of the KMT during the Civil War. Mrs Hou gives an ultimatum to the rest of the tenants to move out on behalf of her husband, who is the "owner" of the flat and who is now planning to sell it. From the conversations with the rest, we find out that Hou has been a Hanjian during the Sino-Japanese War and that he has since taken over the apartment by force from the old landlord, Mr Kong.  The tenants, including Mr Kong, Mrs Xiao, Little Broadcast (alias Mr Xiao, played by Zhao Dan) and a schoolteacher, Mr Hua, and his wife, initially plan to band together, but circumstances force them to find other ways out. Mr Hua tries to find a place to stay at the KMT-sponsored school he is teaching in. Little Broadcast and Mrs Xiao invest in black market gold. As the situation escalates, Mr Hua gets arrested by KMT agents and his young daughter falls desperately ill.

title: Shadow of Angels (Schatten der Engel) (1976)
overview: Beautiful, detached, laconic, consumptive Lily Brest is a streetwalker with few clients. She loves her idle boyfriend Raoul who gambles away what little she earns. The town's power broker, called the rich Jew, discovers she is a good listener, so she's soon busy. Raoul imagines grotesque sex scenes between Lily and the Jew; he leaves her for a man. Her parents, a bitter Fascist who is a cabaret singer in drag and her wheelchair-bound mother, offer no refuge. Even though all have a philosophical bent, the other whores reject Lily because she tolerates everyone, including men. She tires of her lonely life and looks for a way out. Even that act serves the local corrupt powers.

overview: Sarah, 30, single, well educated, likes art, places a voice ad for phone sex, inviting replies from men under 35, sturdy and sensual. Wilbert, a chubby middle aged architect, leaves a message that he is Thomas, 32 and well formed. A week later, she phones. She likes his voice, he likes her laugh, so once a week she phones him (he's not to know her last name, where she lives, or her number). Portraits emerge of humor and sadness. He presses for details of her life and tells her about his work; she wants these Thursday calls to be fantasy and release, separate from the rest of who she is. The film dramatizes these tensions of lies and truth, connection and distance. Written by

title: Venice/Venice (1992)
overview: Dean is a maverick American film director surprised that his most recent film has been chosen as the Official U.S. Entry at the Venice Film Festival. A beautiful French journalist arrives at the festival with the apparent intention of interviewing the unique and eccentric filmmaker. In the midst of all the festival madness, she is forced to confront the wide divergence between things as they really are and things as they seem to be - both on screen and off. And so, finally, are we. Shot half in Venice, Italy and half in Venice, California, "Venice/Venice" looks at the profound effect movies have had - and continue to have - on our lives, our loves and on our dreams of romance.

title: Sexual Life of the Belgians, The (1994)
overview: Jan Bucquoy narrates the story of his sexual life to age 28, imagining his conception (parents drunk, the encounter lasting ten seconds) and reporting his first orgasm (at the hands of Eddy, in a beach-side caravan, as they watch Laurel and Hardy), his comparative experiences with girls, and his move from Harelbeck to Brussels. There he meets Greta, bartender at a Bohemian cafe, who teaches him the Kama Sutra, the naked Esther, who reads him stories, and Thérèse, his wife for three years. They split after two children; he moves to a small flat, writes pornography to pay the bills, works sporadically on a novel, espouses anarchism, and meets more women. His self-confidence grows.

movie_info:
# Cement Garden, The

## Overview
After the death of her husband, the mother of Julie, Jack, Sue, and Tom begins to suffer from a mysterious illness. Aware that she is going to have to go into the hospital, she opens a bank account for the children, ensuring their financial self-sufficiency to avoid being taken into care by the authorities. Unfortunately, she also dies, and Julie and Jack (the older, teenage children) decide to hide her body in the basement to maintain control over their household. As the situation develops, Tom begins dressing as a girl, and Sue becomes increasingly withdrawn, sharing her thoughts only in her diary. Meanwhile, a budding attraction grows between Julie and Jack, but Julie's new boyfriend, Derek, becomes suspicious and poses a threat to their dark family secrets.

## Attributes
- **Genre**: Drama, Psychological Thriller
- **Tags**: Family Dynamics, Grief, Isolation, Forbidden Love, Dark Secrets

## Description
"The Cement Garden" is a haunting exploration of family dysfunction and the lengths to which siblings will go to maintain their fragile autonomy. After the loss of their mother, Julie and Jack's decision to hide her body leads them down a path of psychological complexity, as they navigate their own burgeoning relationship amidst the chaos of their lives. Themes of identity, secrecy, and the impact of grief are woven throughout this unsettling narrative.

title: Hotel de Love (1996)
overview: 10 years ago at a party, Steven thinks he sees the girl of his dreams, Melissa. Just as he's about to make his move, his twin brother Rick gets to her first and they fall in love. Steven watches his brother's relationship bloom, longing for Melissa all the while. Eventually, Melissa leaves to go to college and the brothers go on with their lives. Steven becomes a workaholic to block out his feelings about Melissa and Rick becomes a spineless bellboy at the Hotel de Love, after a later girl friend stood him up at the altar. Enter Steven and Rick's warring parents visiting the Hotel de Love for their anniversary. Re-enter Melissa with her current boyfriend, Norman. Suddenly Rick and Steven have a second chance at Melissa. Also there's Alison the palm reader, Susie behind the counter, the owner/piano player, and the freshly married couple.

# Second Jungle Book: Mowgli & Baloo, The (1997)

## Overview
In this exciting live-action adventure, young Mowgli, an orphan raised by wolves, is spotted by a scout for a giant circus. Accompanied by a cruel hunter and a snake charmer, the scout sets out to trap Mowgli. But with the help of Baloo the bear and Bagheera the panther, little Mowgli leads the adults into his biggest and wildest adventure yet! A fun-filled movie every member of the family will enjoy.

## Attributes
- **Genre**: Adventure, Children
- **Tags**: Family-friendly, Live-action, Jungle adventure, Animal companions, Orphan protagonist

## Description
"Second Jungle Book: Mowgli & Baloo" follows the journey of Mowgli, a young boy raised by wolves in the Indian jungle. When a circus scout discovers him, danger looms as a cruel hunter aims to capture him. With the help of his loyal friends Baloo and Bagheera, Mowgli embarks on a thrilling adventure to evade capture and embrace his wild spirit. The film blends heartwarming friendships with exciting escapades, making it a delightful watch for audiences of all ages.

title: Squeeze (1996)
overview: Benny, a hapless grifter, is thrown off a train after cheating at cards, and into the life of Tanya, a lovely bartender. Tanya has been supporting her husband, a former ballplayer, since his accident, waiting for an insurance settlement that will solve all their financial woes. But when it comes, he refuses to share it with her, claiming with newfound piety that money is the root of all evil. She then enlists the help of Benny to concoct a scheme to get her fair share of the settlement, and he finds one: a local Catholic mission needs money for repairs and Benny decides to create a miracle that will encourage husband Henry to fork over the money - which Benny and Tanya will intercept and share.

# Roseanna's Grave (For Roseanna) (1997)

## Overview
A heartfelt tale of love and sacrifice, where a dying mother's wish to be buried next to her daughter ignites a series of comedic and romantic events.

## Attributes
- **Genre**: Comedy, Romance, Drama
- **Tags**: Heartwarming, Family, Sacrifice, Life and Death, Cemetery, Italian Culture

## Description
"Roseanna's Grave" follows the poignant story of Roseanna, who is facing the end of her life due to a heart condition. Her final wish is to be interred beside her daughter in a rapidly filling cemetery. The plot thickens as Marcello, a compassionate man, strives to prevent any deaths from occurring while Roseanna's thoughts turn toward ensuring Marcello's happiness and future. This film beautifully blends humor and emotion, showcasing the lengths one will go to for love and familial bonds.

- **Tags**: Iranian cinema, Magical realism, Love story, Cultural heritage, Visual storytelling

## Description
"Gabbeh" is a visually stunning exploration of love, tradition, and the stories woven into the fabric of life. The film beautifully blends the mundane activities of an elderly couple with a magical narrative that unfolds through the vibrant designs of their gabbeh, reflecting the deep cultural roots and romantic tales of their clan. The appearance of the young woman serves as a bridge between the past and present, showcasing the timelessness of love and the intricate connections between generations.

title: Innocent Sleep, The (1995)
overview: Inspired by the 1982 Roberto Calvi Affair in which an Italian banker was found hanging from a bridge across the River Thames, the story follows Alan, a man from Northern England who is homeless after the loss of his wife and job. One night while sleeping in a deserted building, Alan witnesses the murder of a high-profile businessman. He attempts to leave the scene unnoticed, but the killers realize that someone has seen them commit the crime. He goes to the police only to discover that one of the killers is leading the case. To stay alive, Alan recruits the help of Billie Hayman, an American journalist, to cover his story.

## Overview

## Attributes
- **Genre**: Crime, Thriller, Drama
- **Tags**: Murder, Conspiracy, Homelessness, Journalism, Survival, Justice

## Description

# For Ever Mozart

## Overview
Episodic film that follows a theater troupe from France attempting to put on a play in Sarajevo. Along their journey they are captured and held in a POW camp, and they call for help from their friends and relations in France.

## Attributes
- **Genre**: Drama, War
- **Tags**: Theater, Sarajevo, POW camp, Friendship, Survival, Artistic Expression

## Description
"For Ever Mozart" is a poignant exploration of the human spirit amidst the chaos of war. The film intricately weaves together the struggles of a French theater troupe as they navigate the challenges of producing a play in a war-torn Sarajevo. Their journey not only highlights the power of art as a means of expression but also delves into themes of friendship and resilience in the face of adversity. The film serves as a commentary on the impact of conflict on creativity and the bonds that sustain individuals during trying times.

# Swept from the Sea

## Overview
The film tells the story of Russian emigree and the only survivor from a ship crash, Yanko Goorall, and servant Amy Foster in the end of the 19th century. When Yanko enters a farm sick and hungry after the shipwreck, everyone is afraid of him, except for Amy, who is very kind and helps him. Soon he becomes like a son to Dr. James Kennedy, and a romance between Yanko and Amy follows.

## Attributes
- **Genre**: Romance, Drama, Historical
- **Tags**: Love Story, Emigration, Shipwreck, 19th Century, Class Differences, Overcoming Prejudice

## Description
"Swept from the Sea" is a poignant romance that explores themes of love and acceptance against the backdrop of societal prejudice. Set in the late 1800s, the film follows Yanko, a Russian emigrant who survives a tragic shipwreck, as he struggles to find refuge and a sense of belonging in a foreign land. His chance encounter with the compassionate Amy Foster leads to a deep connection that defies the fears and biases of those around them. As their relationship develops, the story delves into the complexities of love, identity, and the quest for acceptance in a world filled with misunderstanding.

# Picture Bride

## Overview
Riyo, an orphaned 17-year-old, sails from Yokohama to Hawaii in 1918 to marry Matsuji, a man she has never met. Hoping to escape a troubled past and start anew, Riyo is bitterly disappointed upon her arrival: her husband is twice her age. The miserable girl finds solace with her new friend Kana, a young mother who helps Riyo accept her new life.

## Attributes
- **Genre**: Drama, Romance
- **Tags**: Immigration, Cultural Identity, Friendship, Historical Drama, Women's Rights

## Description
"Picture Bride" is a poignant exploration of love and cultural dislocation, set against the backdrop of early 20th-century Hawaii. Riyo's journey from Japan to a foreign land in search of a better life is marked by unexpected challenges and emotional turmoil. As she grapples with her new reality, Riyo's friendship with Kana becomes a beacon of hope, highlighting themes of resilience, adaptation, and the pursuit of happiness in the face of adversity.

movie_info:
# Caro Diario (Dear Diary)

## Overview
Caro Diario is a 1994 Italian film directed by Nanni Moretti that explores the nuances of daily life through a blend of comedy and drama, presented in a diary format.

## Attributes
- **Genre**: Comedy, Drama
- **Tags**: Slice of Life, Italian Cinema, Irony, Personal Reflection, Friendship, Illness

## Description
In Caro Diario, Nanni Moretti presents three vignettes from his life, each infused with his distinctive ironic perspective. The film opens with him wandering through a desolate Rome, reflecting on the city's beauty and isolation. The second segment takes him to an island where he reconnects with a reclusive friend, exploring themes of solitude and companionship. Finally, he confronts an unknown illness, which serves as a poignant reminder of life's fragility. The film's unique storytelling and introspective narrative make it a standout piece in Italian cinema.

# Sliding Doors

## Overview
London publicist Helen, effortlessly slides between parallel storylines that show what happens when she does or does not catch a train back to her apartment. Love. Romantic entanglements. Deception. Trust. Friendship. Comedy. All come into focus as the two stories shift back and forth, overlap and surprisingly converge.

## Attributes
- **Genre**: Drama, Romance
- **Tags**: Parallel universes, Fate, Relationships, Life choices, Emotional journey, Comedy-drama

## Description
"Sliding Doors" explores the complexities of life and relationships through a unique narrative device that splits the storyline into two distinct paths based on a single moment of chance. When Helen misses a train, her life diverges into two realities: one where she returns home to her boyfriend and another where she finds herself navigating new romantic opportunities and personal challenges. The film poignantly illustrates how small decisions can lead to vastly different outcomes, highlighting themes of love, trust, and self-discovery.

title: Steal Big, Steal Little (1995)
overview: Ruben and Robby are twin brothers, adopted by Mona, one of the wealthiest - and most eccentric - women in Santa Barbara. Ruben is devoted to Mona, but Robby is more devoted to her money. So when Mona leaves her fortune and estate to Ruben it starts a battle between brothers that soon leads to madness, mayhem, and even attempted murder. On Ruben's side is Lou Perilli an ex-Chicago cop and used car dealer who knows the law - and how to get around it. On Robby's side is ruthless businessman Reed Tyler, who is out to turn a swift profit on Mona's property. Walking a shifty line between them is Eddie Agopian, the family lawyer, who doesn't care which side wins as long as he's on the winner's side. But whether they're stealing big or stealing little, they're all stealing in this hilarious comedy about greed, power... and brotherly love.

movie_info:
# Panther

## Overview
Panther is a semi-historic film about the origins of The Black Panther Party for Self-Defense. The movie spans about 3 years (1966-68) of the Black Panther's history in Oakland. Panther also uses historical footage (B/W) to emphasize some points.

## Attributes
- **Genre**: Drama, Historical
- **Tags**: Black Panther Party, Civil Rights, 1960s, Activism, Social Justice, African American History

## Description
Panther chronicles the rise of the Black Panther Party, highlighting significant events and figures within the organization during a tumultuous period in American history. Through a blend of dramatized scenes and actual historical footage, the film aims to educate audiences about the party's mission to combat racial inequality and provide community services, while also addressing the challenges they faced from law enforcement and societal opposition.

# Stars Fell on Henrietta, The (1995)

## Overview
The setting is early America during the oil boom. An elderly, down on his luck 'oil man', Mr. Cox finds himself in the town of Henrietta. Using unconventional methods, he convinces himself and local Don Day that there is oil on Day's land. The financially strapped Day puts everything into finding oil...but at what cost? 

## Attributes
- **Genre**: Drama
- **Tags**: Oil boom, Early America, Financial struggle, Unconventional methods, Small-town dynamics

## Description
Set against the backdrop of the oil boom in early America, "Stars Fell on Henrietta" explores the desperate lengths to which individuals will go to achieve their dreams. Mr. Cox, a seasoned but unsuccessful oil man, partners with Don Day, a local landowner in dire financial straits, to search for oil on Day's property. Their journey is fraught with tension, moral dilemmas, and the harsh realities of ambition, leading them to question the true cost of their aspirations.

# Visitors, The (Visiteurs, Les) (1993)

This outrageous time-travel comedy follows the misadventures of a wacky medieval knight (Jean Reno) and his faithful servant when they are accidentally transported to contemporary times by a senile sorcerer. To avoid being stuck here for good, however, they soon begin an all-out cosmic assault on their former castle -- now a luxury hotel -- in their quest to return to the past.

## Description
In "The Visitors," a bumbling medieval knight and his devoted servant find themselves hilariously out of their depth in the modern world after a sorcerer's spell goes awry. As they navigate contemporary life filled with bizarre technology and social norms, their antics lead to a series of uproarious situations. Determined to return to their time, they concoct a wild plan that involves reclaiming their ancestral home, now a high-end hotel, leading to a chaotic and comedic showdown.

title: Gate of Heavenly Peace, The (1995)
overview: The Gate of Heavenly Peace is a feature-length documentary about the 1989 protest movement, reflecting the drama, tension, humor, absurdity, heroism, and many tragedies of the six weeks from April to June in 1989. The film reveals how the hard-liners within the government marginalized moderates among the protesters (including students, workers and intellectuals), while the actions of radical protesters undermined moderates in the government. Moderate voices were gradually cowed and then silenced by extremism and emotionalism on both sides.

movie_info:
# Gate of Heavenly Peace, The

## Overview
The Gate of Heavenly Peace is a feature-length documentary about the 1989 protest movement, reflecting the drama, tension, humor, absurdity, heroism, and many tragedies of the six weeks from April to June in 1989. The film reveals how the hard-liners within the government marginalized moderates among the protesters (including students, workers, and intellectuals), while the actions of radical protesters undermined moderates in the government. Moderate voices were gradually cowed and then silenced by extremism and emotionalism on both sides.

## Attributes
- **Genre**: Documentary
- **Tags**: 1989 Tiananmen Square, Protest, Social Justice, Historical Events, Political Activism, Chinese History

## Description
This documentary provides an in-depth look at the events surrounding the Tiananmen Square protests of 1989, capturing the complexities of the movement and the struggles between moderate and radical elements on both sides. Through interviews, archival footage, and a nuanced narrative, the film explores the impact of political extremism on the dialogue between the government and the protesters, highlighting the human stories behind one of the most significant events in modern Chinese history.

## Overview
Stressed and overworked, famous French movie star Michel Blanc is beginning to wear down, physically and mentally, from the pressure and demands of fame. Already in a fragile state of mind, strange events start to transpire all around him, and he gradually loses his grip. Taking the advice of a psychiatrist, Blanc retreats to the countryside with his friend Carole Bouquet, but Blanc still has not managed to escape all of his problems.

- **Genre**: Comedy

## Description
In "Grosse Fatigue," Michel Blanc portrays a fictional version of himself, grappling with the absurdities and pressures of celebrity life. As he navigates a series of bizarre occurrences that blur the line between reality and paranoia, the film offers a satirical look at fame and the toll it takes on one's psyche. With the support of his friend Carole Bouquet, Blanc's journey through self-discovery and the quest for peace unfolds humorously and poignantly.

overview: Penurious but muscle-bound Blake Thorne has made a vast fortune marketing health food and health supplements. He once was a nice fellow, but as his wealth increases, he becomes increasingly self-centered and decadent. One day, he gets in a great paint-gun fight that goes too far. Blake escapes the cops by running into a shopping mall, quickly donning a Santa Suit and pretending to be St. Nick. A head injury causes Blake to suffer amnesia, and an opportunistic "elf" decides to convince Blake that he is indeed Santa. This leads "Santa" to help save an orphanage, filled with adorable moppets, from the machinations of a greedy, insane doctor.

# Santa with Muscles

## Overview
Penurious but muscle-bound Blake Thorne has made a vast fortune marketing health food and health supplements. He once was a nice fellow, but as his wealth increases, he becomes increasingly self-centered and decadent. One day, he gets in a great paint-gun fight that goes too far. Blake escapes the cops by running into a shopping mall, quickly donning a Santa Suit and pretending to be St. Nick. A head injury causes Blake to suffer amnesia, and an opportunistic "elf" decides to convince Blake that he is indeed Santa. This leads "Santa" to help save an orphanage, filled with adorable moppets, from the machinations of a greedy, insane doctor.

## Attributes
- **Genre**: Comedy, Family, Holiday
- **Tags**: Christmas, Amnesia, Wealth, Orphanage, Santa Claus, Action-Comedy

## Description
"Santa with Muscles" is a whimsical holiday comedy that follows the journey of Blake Thorne, a wealthy but self-absorbed fitness mogul who, after a series of unfortunate events, finds himself mistaken for Santa Claus. Suffering from amnesia, Blake embraces his new identity and, with the help of a group of children, sets out to thwart the plans of a villainous doctor intent on taking over their orphanage. The film blends slapstick humor with a heartwarming message, making it a unique addition to the holiday movie genre.

However, he doesn't expect his son Timmy, who was living with Ray's sister, to show up at the house right in the middle of planning. Timmy is ignored and Ray and his buddies pull off the heist. Timmy gets his father's attention by stealing the coins and hiding them. To get them back, his father must take him to a number of different places and treat him like he enjoys his presence. They grow fond of each other but Timmy won't stay with his dad unless he gives up the coins.
tagline: ..He's not getting mad, he's Getting Even With Dad.

# Getting Even with Dad

## Overview
A comedic tale of a father-son relationship that develops amidst a backdrop of crime and family bonding.

## Attributes
- **Genre**: Comedy
- **Tags**: Family, Heist, Father-Son Relationship, Crime, Heartwarming

## Description
In "Getting Even with Dad," Ray, a recently released ex-convict and widower, finds his plans for a coin heist disrupted by the unexpected arrival of his young son, Timmy. While Ray and his accomplices execute their scheme to finance a bakery, Timmy feels neglected and decides to take the stolen coins for himself. This sparks a series of adventures as Ray must engage with Timmy to retrieve the coins, leading to a heartfelt journey of rediscovery and bonding between father and son.

# Jefferson in Paris

## Overview
His wife having recently died, Thomas Jefferson accepts the post of United States ambassador to pre-revolutionary France, though he finds it difficult to adjust to life in a country where the aristocracy subjugates an increasingly restless peasantry. In Paris, he becomes smitten with cultured artist Maria Cosway, but, when his daughter visits from Virginia accompanied by her attractive slave, Sally Hemings, Jefferson's attentions are diverted.

## Attributes
- **Genre**: Drama, Historical
- **Tags**: Thomas Jefferson, Paris, Romance, American History, 18th Century, Diplomacy, Slavery, French Revolution

## Description
"Jefferson in Paris" explores the complexities of Thomas Jefferson's life as he navigates his role as an ambassador in a politically charged France. Struggling with personal loss, Jefferson is torn between his affections for the artist Maria Cosway and his daughter’s visit, which brings with it the presence of Sally Hemings, raising questions of love, loyalty, and moral conflict against the backdrop of an evolving society.

# Cosi

## Overview
Lewis, a young amateur theater director, is offered a job with a governmental program for the rehabilitation of mentally ill patients in a Sydney institution. His project is overrun by one of the patients who wants to stage the opera Cosi Fan Tutte by Mozart despite the fact that none of the patients are able to sing and none of them speak Italian. A comedy of errors ensues, but one which unifies the patients and their director in unexpected ways.

## Attributes
- **Genre**: Comedy, Drama
- **Tags**: Rehabilitation, Mental Health, Opera, Theatrical, Ensemble Cast, Sydney, Adaptation

## Description
In "Cosi," Lewis takes on the challenging task of directing a production within a mental health facility, where the patients' unique perspectives and struggles lead to both comedic and heartfelt moments. The attempt to produce Mozart's opera Cosi Fan Tutte becomes a transformative experience for both Lewis and the patients, showcasing their resilience, creativity, and the healing power of art amidst the chaos of their lives.

In "It Takes Two," two identical girls, one an orphan and the other from a privileged background, accidentally meet at summer camp. Realizing they could solve their problems by swapping places, they embark on a comedic adventure filled with misunderstandings and heartfelt moments. Their ultimate goal is to bring together Alyssa's father and Amanda's caring social worker, showcasing the power of friendship and the importance of family.

# Shadows (Cienie) (1988)

## Overview
During the Second World War, tens of thousands of blonde, blue-eyed Polish children were snatched from their parents and given to German families. Lebensborn was part of Hitler's plan to expand the Aryan master race within the Third Reich. Eight-year old Jerzy returns home at the end of the war to a joyful reunion with his long-lost mother and grandfather. But problems arise as he is taunted by his peers and, longing for his missing father, burns with resentment for his new communist stepfather.

## Attributes
- **Genre**: Drama, War
- **Tags**: WWII, Family, Identity, Trauma, Resentment, Historical, Polish Cinema

## Description
"Shadows" delves into the harrowing aftermath of war as it follows the journey of young Jerzy, who faces the painful struggle of reintegrating into a world that has changed drastically during his absence. The film poignantly explores themes of identity, belonging, and the scars left by both familial loss and societal upheaval, painting a vivid portrait of a child's turmoil in the face of historical atrocities.

title: Aparajito (1956)
overview: Aparajito picks up where the first film leaves off, with Apu and his family having moved away from the country to live in the bustling holy city of Varanasi (then known as Benares). As Apu progresses from wide-eyed child to intellectually curious teenager, eventually studying in Kolkata, we witness his academic and moral education, as well as the growing complexity of his relationship with his mother. This tenderly expressive, often heart-wrenching film, which won three top prizes at the Venice Film Festival, including the Golden Lion, not only extends but also spiritually deepens the tale of Apu.  Preserved by the Academy Film Archive in 1996.

title: Tigrero: A Film That Was Never Made (1994)
original_title: Tigrero: A Film That Was Never Made
overview: In 1993, Sam Fuller takes Jim Jarmusch on a trip into Brazil's Mato Grosso, up the River Araguaia to the village of Santa Isabel Do Morro, where 40 years before, Zanuck had sent Fuller to scout a location and write a script for a movie based on a tigrero, a jaguar hunter. Sam hopes to find people who remember him, and he takes film he shot in 1954. He's Rip Van Winkle, and, indeed, a great deal changed in the village. There are televisions, watches, and brick houses. But, the same Karajá culture awaits as well. He gathers the villagers to show his old film footage, and people recognize friends and relatives, thanking Fuller for momentarily bringing them back to life.

movie_info:
# Eye of Vichy, The (Oeil de Vichy, L') (1993)

## Overview
Directed by French filmmaker Claude Chabrol, this documentary examines Nazi and Vichy newsreels and propaganda films from World War II meant to turn the French against the Jews and the Allied Forces and into Nazi sympathizers. This movie is only made of archive pictures: the official newsreels that were broadcasted on French movie screens during 1940 and 1944 (the Occupation).

## Attributes
- **Genre**: Documentary, Historical
- **Tags**: World War II, Propaganda, Vichy France, Nazi Germany, History, Archive Footage

## Description
"Eye of Vichy" presents a compelling and unsettling look at the propaganda machine of Vichy France during World War II, utilizing only archival footage to portray how the regime manipulated public perception. The film serves as both a historical document and a cautionary tale about the power of media in shaping societal attitudes, particularly regarding anti-Semitism and nationalism.

title: Daens (1992)
overview: In the 1890s, Father Adolf Daens goes to Aalst, a textile town where child labor is rife, pay and working conditions are horrible, the poor have no vote, and the Catholic church backs the petite bourgeoisie in oppressing workers. He writes a few columns for the Catholic paper, and soon workers are listening and the powerful are in an uproar. He's expelled from the Catholic party, so he starts the Christian Democrats and is elected to Parliament. After Rome disciplines him, he must choose between two callings, as priest and as champion of workers. In subplots, a courageous young woman falls in love with a socialist and survives a shop foreman's rape; children die; prelates play billiards.

# Daens

## Overview
In the 1890s, Father Adolf Daens confronts the harsh realities of child labor and oppression in a textile town, leading him to advocate for the rights of workers against the backdrop of a reluctant Church.

## Attributes
- **Genre**: Drama, Historical, Biographical
- **Tags**: Labor Rights, Social Justice, Religion, 19th Century, Activism, Belgian Cinema

## Description
"Daens" tells the compelling story of Father Adolf Daens, who arrives in Aalst to witness the dire conditions of workers, particularly children, laboring in the textile industry. As he begins to champion their cause, he faces opposition from both the Church and local authorities. His journey from priest to political activist highlights the struggle for social change in a rapidly industrializing society, while intertwining personal stories of love and survival against the odds.

title: Quartier Mozart (1992)
overview: The boisterous and cheerful lives of the residents of Cameroon are barely dented by incursions of supernatural power in this humor-filled rendition of traditional folk tales in modern guise. In the story, a cheerfully naughty girl crosses paths with a witch who has the power to satisfy her curiosity about men by changing her into a young man. She then becomes one of the boy suitors for the amorous attentions of a policeman's daughter. Some of the men have unusual names and even odder magical gifts: one of them has the ability to make a man's genitals disappear when he shakes hands with him.

title: Salut cousin! (1996)
overview: The comedy in this lively film barely conceals its darker, more serious undertones as it chronicles a young Algerian's eye-opening introduction to the joys and travails of being an immigrant in Paris. Alilo has left his home to pick up an important suitcase for his employer. Unfortunately, he has lost the Parisian address. Fortunately, his cousin Mok, emigrated there several years before with his middle-class family before and is able to act as a guide. Mok, an aspiring rap singer, comes from a middle-class family, but chooses to live on his own in the dilapidated deteriorating 18th district, known as 'Moskova.' Mok characterizes the place as a haven for artists and intellectuals, but it is plainly just a Third World slum filled with tightly knit and colorful neighbors. Mok and Alilo have many interesting, some tragedy-tinged adventures over the five days it takes them to find the suitcase.

title: Love Serenade (1996)
overview: In Sunray, a backwater town on Australia's Murray River, there's little to do but fish or listen to the local radio station. D.J. Ken Sherry arrives from the hustle of Brisbane to run the station; he's mid-40s, detached, thrice divorced, hatchet faced. # Love Serenade

## Overview
In Sunray, a backwater town on Australia's Murray River, there's little to do but fish or listen to the local radio station. D.J. Ken Sherry arrives from the hustle of Brisbane to run the station; he's mid-40s, detached, thrice divorced, hatchet faced. Both sisters next door find him attractive: awkward Dimity, only 20, who works in a Chinese restaurant with few patrons, and perky Vicki-Ann, a hairdresser with a hope chest who invents a happy future with Sherry based on little but his arrival.

## Attributes
- **Genre**: Comedy, Drama, Romance
- **Tags**: Small Town, Love Triangle, Radio, Sisters, Quirky Characters, Australian Cinema

## Description
"Love Serenade" is a quirky romantic comedy that explores the complexities of love and desire in a sleepy Australian town. When the jaded D.J. Ken Sherry arrives, he unwittingly becomes the object of affection for two sisters, leading to an awkward and humorous love triangle. As both women navigate their feelings for Ken, the film delves into themes of longing, ambition, and the sometimes absurd nature of love, all set against the backdrop of a charming, yet isolated community.

# Deceiver

## Overview
The gruesome death of a prostitute brings suspicion on one of her clients, James Wayland, a brilliant, self-destructive and epileptic heir to a textile fortune. So detectives Braxton and Kennesaw take Wayland in for questioning, thinking they can break the man. But despite his troubles, Wayland is a master of manipulation, and during the interrogation, he begins to turn the tables on the investigators, forcing them to reveal their own sinister sides.

## Attributes
- **Genre**: Crime, Thriller, Mystery
- **Tags**: Psychological, Interrogation, Manipulation, Dark themes, Heir, Detectives

## Description
"Deceiver" unfolds as an intense psychological thriller that captures the intricate dance between a cunning suspect and the detectives determined to crack him. As James Wayland navigates through his own turbulent psyche, the film delves into themes of deception, moral ambiguity, and the darker aspects of human nature. The interrogation scenes serve as a battleground for wits, revealing not only the depths of Wayland's character but also the flawed motivations of those seeking the truth.

# Intimate Relations

## Overview
In 1950s England, sailor Harold Guppy arrives in a small seaside town looking for his estranged brother. After a brief reunion, Harold finds a room for rent in the house of Mrs. Beasley, her meek husband, and their teenage daughter, Joyce. It's clear that Harold has a troubled past, but his future is about to get more perilous yet. Despite the rosy surface, Harold soon finds himself in a tawdry sexual tug-of-war that won't end well.

## Attributes
- **Genre**: Comedy, Drama, Romance
- **Tags**: Dark comedy, British cinema, 1950s, Adult themes, Family dynamics

## Description
"Intimate Relations" is a darkly comedic exploration of human relationships set against the backdrop of post-war England. The film follows Harold Guppy, whose quest to reconnect with his brother leads him into a web of complex interactions with the Beasley family. As Harold's past begins to unravel, the seemingly mundane life in the seaside town reveals its hidden tensions and desires, resulting in an unpredictable and often humorous struggle for intimacy and connection.

title: Leading Man, The (1996)
overview: Successful playwright Felix Webb has a new play, 'The Hit Man', in rehearsal. Directed by his old friend Humphrey, it is already being hailed as a masterpiece; but Felix can't enjoy his success. He has fallen passionately in love with Hilary, a beautiful, fiesty young actress, and is preparing to desert his perfect family, his wife Elena and three lively children. His intolerable situation is further complicated when Humphrey casts Hilary as one of the leads in 'The Hit Man'. Enter Robin Grange, a charismatic young Hollywood actor making his London theatre debut. Robin is attractive, charming and dangerous, and soon inveigles his way into everyone's life. He ingratiates himself with the cast and, quickly grasping Felix's dilemma, sets about weaving his web of mischief. He suggests that if he were to seduce Elena, she would be distracted from Felix's affair, regain her self respect, and perhaps even willingly part from the unfaithful husband to whom she clings...
tagline: Indecent. Immoral. Irresistible. It's the role he was born to play.

## Description
In "The Leading Man," successful playwright Felix Webb struggles with his passion for young actress Hilary while grappling with the responsibilities of his family. As rehearsals for his new play, "The Hit Man," unfold, Felix finds himself at a crossroads, torn between his idyllic life with his wife Elena and their three children, and his burgeoning love for Hilary. The plot thickens with the arrival of charismatic Hollywood actor Robin Grange, who manipulates the situation to his advantage, suggesting that seducing Elena might be the key to untangling Felix's predicament. ## Overview
A young man, Ryan, suffering from a disability, wishes to join the other kids from his school's football team. During an initiation rite, Ryan is swept away through a whirlpool to the land of Tao. Ryan is rescued by the protectors of Tao, five humanoid kangaroos, each imbued with the five elements and virtues. Ryan learns his valuable lesson while saving the land of Tao.

- **Genre**: Action, Adventure, Children, Fantasy
- **Tags**: Fantasy adventure, Hero's journey, Coming-of-age, Magical creatures, Empowerment

## Description
"Warriors of Virtue" takes viewers on a fantastical journey as Ryan, a boy with a disability, discovers his inner strength in the mystical land of Tao. As he encounters five courageous kangaroo warriors, each representing a unique virtue, he learns the importance of bravery, friendship, and self-acceptance while battling the wicked Lord Komodo. This family-friendly film combines action and fantasy elements, promoting themes of perseverance and courage.

# Butterfly Kiss

## Overview
Deeply mentally unbalanced drifter Eunice roams grim northern Britain committing psychosexual serial murders of both men and women while ostensibly searching for an unknown woman named Judith. She spares the life of lonely but kind-hearted gas station cashier Miriam, who abandons her dismal life to follow her damaged new lover. While attempting to hide the evidence of her multiple crimes, Miriam tries to understand Eunice's bizarre quest.

## Attributes
- **Genre**: Thriller, Psychological Horror, Crime
- **Tags**: Serial Killer, Mental Illness, Obsession, Dark Romance, Northern England

## Description
"Butterfly Kiss" is a chilling exploration of obsession and the darker aspects of human nature. The film follows Eunice, a disturbed drifter whose search for a mysterious woman leads her down a path of violence and chaos. As she becomes entwined with Miriam, a lonely cashier drawn to Eunice's tumultuous persona, the story delves into themes of love, identity, and the complexities of sanity. Hush is a gripping psychological thriller that explores the dark depths of family dynamics and jealousy. As Helen tries to navigate the complexities of her new life with Jackson and his overbearing mother, Martha, the tension escalates into a chilling battle for Jackson's love and loyalty. movie_info:
# Lamerica

## Overview
Fiore, an Italian conman, arrives in post Communist Albania with Gino, his young apprentice, to set up a shoe factory that will never open. The con requires a native Albanian, so they designate Spiro, an impoverished and confused former political prisoner as chairman of the board. When Fiore returns to Italy to get government funds for the project, Spiro unexpectedly disappears and Gino sets out on a journey to find him. The search leads him to discover Spiro's tragic personal history and witness Albanian poverty firsthand. 

## Attributes
- **Genre**: Drama
- **Tags**: Conman, Albania, Post-Communism, Social Issues, Journey, Poverty, Political History

## Description
"Lamerica" is a poignant exploration of the aftermath of communism in Albania, seen through the eyes of an Italian conman and his apprentice. As they navigate the complexities of deception and exploitation, Gino's journey transforms from a simple quest to locate Spiro into a profound awakening to the harsh realities and struggles faced by the Albanian people. The film delicately intertwines themes of hope and despair, leaving a lasting impact on its audience.

# Nico Icon

## Overview
A look into the many lives of Christa Päffgen, otherwise known as Nico; from cutie German mädchen to the first of the supermodels, to glamorous diva of the Velvet Underground, to cult item, junkie and hag. Many faces for the same woman, whom, you realize, just couldn't bring herself to care enough to live.

## Attributes
- **Genre**: Documentary, Biography, Music
- **Tags**: Nico, Velvet Underground, Supermodels, Addiction, Music History, Cultural Icon

## Description
"Nico Icon" delves into the complex and multifaceted life of Christa Päffgen, famously known as Nico. The documentary explores her evolution from a young German model to a prominent figure in the music world, particularly as a member of the Velvet Underground. Through interviews, archival footage, and a reflective narrative, the film paints a poignant portrait of a woman who struggled with fame, addiction, and her own identity, ultimately revealing the tragic beauty of her existence.

# Land and Freedom (Tierra y libertad) (1995)

## Overview
David Carr is a British Communist who is unemployed. In 1936, when the Spanish Civil War begins, he decides to fight for the Republican side, a coalition of liberals, communists and anarchists, so he joins the POUM militia and witnesses firsthand the betrayal of the Spanish revolution by Stalin's followers and Moscow's orders.

## Attributes
- **Genre**: War, Drama, Historical
- **Tags**: Spanish Civil War, Communism, Political Struggle, Militia, Betrayal, Revolution, Ideological Conflict

## Description
"Land and Freedom" is a poignant exploration of the Spanish Civil War through the eyes of David Carr, a British volunteer who becomes deeply involved in the struggle against fascism. As he joins the POUM militia, the film highlights the complexities of revolutionary politics and the disillusionment that arises from internal conflicts and external pressures, particularly from Stalinist factions. The narrative not only captures the chaos of war but also delves into the philosophical and moral dilemmas faced by those fighting for their beliefs.

title: Brothers in Trouble (1995)
overview: Amir is an illegal Pakistani immigrant smuggled into England in the 1960's to work, to send money to his family and perhaps even bring them over with him. A skilled laborer, he is forced to do unskilled work like shoveling sheep dung and processing wool. He lives in a boarding house with nearly a dozen other men, under the supervision of Hussein Shah. He befriends a young student, Sakib, who dreams of being a writer. Their existence is punctuated by secret movies, a visiting prostitute, fear of detection and deportation, and the gangster-like smuggler who comes by for his take every week. The household is shaken up by the arrival of a white girl, Shah's girlfriend, and the sense of femininity and family she brings.

## Attributes
- **Genre**: Drama
- **Tags**: Immigration, Friendship, Struggle, Cultural Identity, 1960s, British Cinema

## Description
In the heart of 1960s England, Amir, a Pakistani illegal immigrant, faces the relentless challenges of adapting to a new life. Smuggled into the country to provide for his family back home, he finds himself performing menial labor under difficult conditions and living in cramped quarters with fellow immigrants. Amidst the backdrop of fear and longing, he befriends Sakib, a young student with aspirations of becoming a writer. Their lives take unexpected turns with the arrival of a woman who brings a sense of femininity and warmth into their harsh existence, complicating their relationships and dreams.

title: Eighth Day, The (1996)
overview: Georges has Down syndrome, living at a mental-institution, Harry is a busy businessman, giving lectures for young aspiring salesmen. He is successful in his business life, but his social life is a disaster since his wife left him and took their two children with her. This weekend his children came by train to meet him, but Harry, working as always, forgot to pick them up. Neither his wife or his children want to see him again and he is driving around on the country roads, anguished and angry. He almost runs over Georges, on the run from the institution since everybody else went home with their parents except him, whose mother is dead. Harry tries to get rid of Georges but he won't leave his new friend. Eventually a special friendship forms between the two of them, a friendship which makes Harry a different person.

Interviews in the Michael Moore/"Roger and Me" tradition examine life in small-town America, class conflicts and the collapse of an upstate New York community, Dadetown, when the town's once-prosperous factory, reduced to the manufacture of paper clips and staples, finally closes. Facing massive unemployment, the blue-collar Dadetown residents next find yuppies moving into town to staff the local division of a big computer outfit.

## Attributes
- **Genre**: Documentary
- **Tags**: Small-town America, Class Conflict, Social Commentary, Economic Decline, Community, Interviews

## Description
"Dadetown" provides a poignant look at the struggles and transformations within a small American town as it grapples with industrial decline and the influx of new residents from different socioeconomic backgrounds. The documentary captures the personal stories of former factory workers who face the harsh realities of unemployment and changing community dynamics, highlighting the tensions between the old blue-collar lifestyle and the emerging white-collar presence.

movie_info:
# The Big One

## Overview
The Big One is an investigative documentary from director Michael Moore who goes around the country asking why big American corporations produce their product abroad where labor is cheaper while so many Americans are unemployed, losing their jobs, and would happily be hired by such companies as Nike.

## Attributes
- **Genre**: Comedy, Documentary
- **Tags**: Social Commentary, Labor Issues, Corporate Accountability, American Economy, Critique of Capitalism

## Description
In "The Big One," Michael Moore embarks on a cross-country journey to uncover the reasons behind the outsourcing of American jobs. Through a blend of humor and poignant interviews, Moore challenges corporate practices and highlights the struggles of American workers who are left jobless, all while major corporations reap high profits by exploiting cheaper labor abroad. The film serves as a compelling critique of capitalism and raises important questions about corporate responsibility and the future of the American workforce.

Horror, Action, Sci-Fi, Thriller, Violence, Supernatural, War, Fantasy

title: Scream of Stone (Schrei aus Stein) (1991)
overview: A meeting of two world famous climbers, one an experienced mountaineer the other a sport climber, and a journalist (Ivan) results in a bet on which of the two is the best climber. Roger (the mountaineering expert) states that Martin (the sport climber) wouldn't survive a day on a 'real' climbing expedition, although he is considered to be the world's best sport climber (having just won an indoor 'world championship,' an event depicted in the opening scene). They plan to climb 'Cerro Torre,' in the Patagonia region of South America, near the Argentinian/Chilean border, one of the world's most difficult mountains, especially considering the extreme weather conditions common to the area.

movie_info:
# Scream of Stone (Schrei aus Stein)

## Overview
A meeting of two world famous climbers, one an experienced mountaineer and the other a sport climber, leads to a bet on who is the superior climber.

## Attributes
- **Genre**: Drama, Adventure
- **Tags**: Climbing, Competition, Survival, Mountaineering, Sports, Patagonia

## Description
"Scream of Stone" follows the intense rivalry between Roger, a seasoned mountaineer, and Martin, a top sport climber, as they embark on an ambitious expedition to conquer Cerro Torre, one of the toughest mountains in the world. Amidst breathtaking landscapes and the challenges posed by extreme weather, the film explores themes of ambition, the spirit of competition, and the essence of true climbing prowess.

## Dislikes:
- Horror
- Comedy
- Fantasy
- Sci-Fi
- Romance
